value.value: A cellular carbohydrate catabolic process that converts a carbohydrate to pyruvate and either glyceraldehyde or glyceraldehyde-3 phosphate by dehydration and aldol cleavage via a gluconate or 6-phosphogluconate intermediate.
The Entner-Doudoroff pathway that proceeds through a D-gluconate intermediate.

label.value: Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde

value.value: The Entner-Doudoroff pathway that proceeds through a D-gluconate intermediate and yields pyruvate and D-glyceraldehyde.

label.value: Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate

value.value: The Entner-Doudoroff pathway that proceeds through a D-gluconate intermediate and yields pyruvate and D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate.
The process in which the anatomical structures of a seminal vesicle are generated and organized.

label.value: branching involved in seminal vesicle morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the branching structure of the seminal vesicle is generated and organized. A branch is a division or offshoot from a main stem.

The autophagy process which begins when chaperones and co-chaperones recognize a target motif and unfold the substrate protein. The proteins are then transported to the lysosome where they are degraded.
Catalysis of the reaction: diphthine methyl ester + H2O = diphthine + H+ + methanol.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-cysteine + N-alpha,N-alpha,N-alpha-trimethyl-L-histidine (hercynine) + O2 = hercynylcysteine sulfoxide + H2O.

Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of inorganic compounds. These include transport of such compounds away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of inorganic compounds.

A glycolytic process in which the glucose is catabolized to pyruvate by first entering the Entner-Doudoroff pathway to yield pyruvate and glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate. The glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate is subsequently converted to pyruvate by the core glycolytic enzymes.

An specialized occluding junction where three epithelial cells meet. It is composed of a branching network of sealing strands that run perpendicularly to the bicellular tight junction at the point of contact between three epithelial cells in an epithelial sheet.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + N(6)-[(R)-lipoyl]-L-lysyl-[lipoyl-carrier protein] = (R)-lipoate + L-lysyl-[lipoyl-carrier protein].

Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of hydrogen peroxide. These include transport of hydrogen peroxide away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration.

Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of hydrogen peroxide in a cell. These include transport of hydrogen peroxide away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + methylphosphonate = alpha-D-ribose 1-methylphosphonate 5-triphosphate + adenine.
A catalytic protein complex that is capable of alpha-D-ribose 1-methylphosphonate 5-triphosphate synthase activity.

definition.value: An example of this complex is PhnI (P16687) in Escherichia coli.

value.value: A transferase complex capable of catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
A protein complex that is a protein hormone secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary of vertebrates. capable of regulating normal growth, sexual development, and reproductive function.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + N(6)-glutaryl-L-lysyl-[protein] + NAD+ = 2''-O-glutaryl-ADP-D-ribose + L-lysyl-[protein] + nicotinamide.

definition.value: This reaction is the removal of a glutaryl group from a glutarylated lysine residue of a protein or peptide.

value.value: The removal of a glutaryl group (CO-CH2-CH2-CH2-CO) from a residue in a peptide or protein.

A multiprotein subcomplex of the GATOR complex that regulates TORC1 signaling by interacting with the Rag GTPase. In human, this complex consists of WDR24, WDR59, MIOS, SEH1L, and SEC13. In S. cerevisiae, this complex is referred to as SEACAT and contains the Sea2p, Sea3p, Sea4p, Seh1p, Sec13p proteins.

definition.value: The Rag GTPase complex corresponds to Gtr1-Gtr2 GTPase complex ; GO:1990131.

value.value: A spherical, bilayered proteolipid vesicle released from gram-negative bacterial outer membranes.
A cytosolic protein complex that is capable of activating caspase-1.
A protein complex that consists of an assemble of ASC dimers that is capable of inducing pyroptosis.

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a sucrose into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP and the reduction of NAD(P) to NAD(P)H. Glycolysis begins with the metabolism of a carbohydrate to generate products that can enter the pathway and ends with the production of pyruvate. Pyruvate may be converted to acetyl-coenzyme A, ethanol, lactate, or other small molecules.

label.value: sucrose catabolic process to fructose-6-phosphate through glucose and fructose

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of sucrose, to yield fructose-6-phosphate through both glucose and fructose intermediates.

label.value: glycolytic process from sucrose through glucose and fructose

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of sucrose into pyruvate through both glucose and fructose intermediates, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP and the reduction of NAD(P) to NAD(P)H. Glycolysis begins with the metabolism of a carbohydrate to generate products that can enter the pathway and ends with the production of pyruvate. Pyruvate may be converted to acetyl-coenzyme A, ethanol, lactate, or other small molecules.
The single-organism macropinocytosis process that results in the uptake of an extracellular exosome.

Catalysis of 5-taurinomethyluridine in tRNA + a [protein]-S-sulfanylcysteine + ATP + a reduced electron acceptor = a 5-taurinomethyl-2-thiouridine in tRNA + a [protein]-L-cysteine + AMP + an oxidized electron acceptor + diphosphate + H+.
The selective autohagy process in which parts of the endoplasmic reticulum are loaded into autophagosomes, delivered to the vacuole, and degraded in response to changing cellular conditions.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-threonine + ATP + bicarbonate = L-threonylcarbamoyladenylate + diphosphate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-threonylcarbamoyladenylate + adenine(37) in tRNA = AMP + N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine(37) in tRNA.

Catalysis of the reaction: N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine(37) in tRNA + sulfur-(sulfur carrier) + 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine = 2-methylthio-N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine(37) in tRNA + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (sulfur carrier) + L-methionine + 5'-deoxyadenosine.
The step in the formation of the neural tube, where the paired anterior neural folds are brought together and fuse at the dorsal midline.
Combining selectively with extracellular folic acid and delivering it into the cell via endocytosis.
The directed movement of a processed miRNA from the nucleus to the cytoplasm.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose, with the production of pyruvate.

label.value: glucose catabolic process to pyruvate utilizing ADP

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP and the utilization of ADP in the initial kinase reactions.

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of 6-sulfoquinovose(1-) resulting in the formation of glycerone phosphate (DHAP) and 3-sulfolactaldehyde (SLA).
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of 6-sulfoquinovose(1-) resulting in the formation of glycerone phosphate (DHAP) and 3-sulfopropanediol(1-).
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of 6-sulfoquinovose(1-) resulting in the formation of glycerone phosphate (DHAP) and pyruvate.
The selective degradation of glycogen by macroautophagy.
The selective degradation of lipid droplets by macroautophagy.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipid droplets and hydrolysis of stored triglycerides occurring through the orchestrated activation of cytosolic lipases.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of methylglyoxal, CH3-CO-CHO, into lactate.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of GDP-mannose from mannose.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of GDP-mannose from fructose-6-phosphate.
Binding to C-rich, single-stranded, telomere-associated DNA.
Catalysis of the formation of 2'-deoxyribonucleoside diphosphate from ribonucleoside diphosphate, using either thioredoxin disulfide or glutaredoxin disulfide as an acceptor.
